		<p class="faq"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>My posts aren’t previewing!</p>
		<p>
			<strong>Sometimes, the “Preview” button sends you to page with a URL that looks like this:</strong>
		</p>
		<p>http://<% if current_user.school.shortname != 'national' %><%= current_user.school.shortname %>.<% end %>spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&amp;p=74&amp;preview=true&amp;preview_id=74&amp;preview_nonce=e9be8a35ed&amp;post_format=standard</p>
		<p>
			<strong>which leads to a page that says, ‘Page Not Found’, but the preview is actually here:</strong>
		</p>
		<p>http://<% if current_user.school.shortname != 'national' %><%= current_user.school.shortname %>.<% end %>spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&amp;p=74&amp;preview=true&amp;preview_id=74&amp;preview_nonce=e9be8a35ed</p>
		<p><strong>(Which is the original link without the ‘&amp;post_format=standard’ on the end). So if you go to the original link and delete that last section on the end:</strong></p>
		<p>http://<% if current_user.school.shortname != 'national' %><%= current_user.school.shortname %>.<% end %>spoonuniversity.com/?post_type=recipe&amp;p=74&amp;preview=true&amp;preview_id=74&amp;preview_nonce=e9be8a35ed<strong>&amp;post_format=standard</strong>
		</p>
		<p><strong>Then you’ll be able to preview your post!<br>
			We’re looking into a more permanent fix, but this should help for now!</strong></p>
			<p class="faq"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>My photos are too small!</p>
			<p>Find the dimensions of the file. On a Mac, Finder will show you the dimensions in the file info:<br>
				<img alt="" src="/assets/finderdimensions.png">
				<br>
				If the dimensions of the file are too small, then you need to go back to an earlier version of the image when it is bigger (maybe directly off your camera card?).* If the file dimensions are not too small, then you’re just cropping it incorrectly. Try editing the image size in Photoshop, or cropping it in iPhoto, or even heading over to <a target="_blank" href="http://www.picresize.com/">picresize.com</a>. Remember, the images always need to be at least 770px across (no larger than 1024px across).</p>
				<p class="?">*Despite what it may seem like in all of those TNT Drama shows where the cops zoom in on old video recordings to see someone’s license plates really far away, images can’t be made larger than their dimensions without getting pixelated and blurry.</p>
				<p>If that doesn’t work, try watching this video:</p>
				<p>
					<iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/81032625" width="640" height="400" frameborder="0" title="Photos too small" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen="" kwframeid="1">
					</iframe>
				</p>
