						<p class="faq"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>What do I do if I’m shooting in the dark?</p>
						<p>Is there <em>any way</em> that you can take these photos at a different time when there <em>is</em> natural light? Please, please do that. If not, try to move all of the lights in the room to where you’re shooting. You can move them back later. Don’t have one lamp with piercing light reflecting off of your plate. Be resourceful and creative, and try to edit the photo to account for the darkness.</p>
						<p class="faq"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>What do I do if my photos are yellowed?</p>
						<p>Brighten them, then cool them down with blue tones.</p>
